A rare disease called multisystem inflammatory syndrome (MIS-C) is being recorded in some  children who have contracted Covid-19, CNN reports. The US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention reported 2,617 MIS-C cases and 33 deaths among children before March 1, an increase from Februaryâ€™s 2,060 cases and 30 deaths. The cause of MIS-C is unknown and doctors report children often contract Covid-19 before presenting symptoms, but this is not always the case. TimesLIVE